---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'
import Layout from '../layouts/Page.astro'
import me from '../assets/me.jpg'
---

<Layout title='About' description='About Michelangelo Markus and this site.'>
    <Image src={me} alt="Michelangelo Markus" class="bio-photo" width={150} densities={[1, 2]} />
    <p>
        I'm Michelangelo, a Senior Cloud Consultant at superluminar in Berlin.
        The harder problems lately are in generative AI, alongside a deepening
        interest in cloud sovereignty and what it means to keep workloads under
        European control. Most of the work is still on AWS.
    </p>
    <p>
        The route here wasn't a straight line. Two years teaching computer
        science in Cambodia, then retraining into engineering through BloomTech,
        three years as a public-sector Solutions Architect at AWS (Central SA,
        then NPO Research), some independent consulting, and eventually Berlin.
    </p>
    <p>
        I write about what surprises me. Right now that's the layer above the
        harness: what breaks at the seams when one agent has to trust another,
        what identity and delegation actually mean across managed runtimes, and
        the measurements that would let any of this be engineered rather than
        asserted. Cloud sovereignty is the other thread I keep returning to.
    </p>
    <p>
        Off-screen I'm rarely in my own time zone. Motorcycles, music festivals,
        and bouldering when I am.
    </p>
    <p>
        <a href='mailto:m@michelangelo.codes'>m@michelangelo.codes</a>
    </p>
</Layout>

<style>
	/* Portrait floated beside the bio on wider screens; stacks on top on
	   narrow ones so it never crowds the text. */
	.bio-photo {
		float: right;
		width: 140px;
		height: 140px;
		object-fit: cover;
		border-radius: 18px;
		margin: 0 0 1rem 1.5rem;
	}
	@media (max-width: 32rem) {
		.bio-photo {
			float: none;
			margin: 0 0 1.5rem 0;
		}
	}
</style>
